    <worksheet name='Detailed Demographic Heatmap (2)'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='20'>Demographic Bullying Hotspots by Protected Harassment Category </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='12'>Compare reported students affected by race-based and sex-based harassment across U.S. states, demographic groups, and gender.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
        <caption>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>📊 Demographic Bullying Hotspots by State</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>Purpose</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>
Compare demographic bullying patterns across U.S. states by analyzing </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>race-based</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'> and </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>sex-based</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'> harassment.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>How to Read</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>Rows:</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'> U.S. states</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>Columns:</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'> Student demographic groups, separated by </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>Female</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'> and </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>Male</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>Protected Category:</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'> Selects the harassment type (</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>Race</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'> or </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>Sex</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>)</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>Color:</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'> Darker cells indicate higher numbers of reported affected students.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>Tooltip:</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'> Displays reported students and disciplinary actions.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>Why only Race and Sex?</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>
The CRDC provides detailed demographic breakdowns </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>only for Race- and Sex-based harassment</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>. Other harassment categories are available in the dataset but are reported only as aggregated totals and therefore cannot be analyzed at the same demographic level.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>Key Insight</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau lite' fontsize='10'>
Compare how reported bullying affects different demographic groups across states to identify potential disparities and areas for further investigation. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
