    <worksheet name='State Overview Map'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='20'>Normalized Bullying Reporting Rate by State</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000'>Reported bullying allegations per school, used to compare states of different sizes.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
        <caption>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='10'>📄 State Overview Map</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='10'>Purpose</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='10'>Shows where reported bullying allegations are concentrated across U.S. states using a normali zed reporting rate.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='10'>Methodology</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='10'>The metric is calculated as total reported allegations divided by the number of school records in each state. This avoids comparing states only by raw totals, since larger states naturally have more schools.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='10'>Key Insight</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='10'>Darker states show higher reported allegations per school. This highlights reporting intensity, not confirmed bullying prevalence or school performance.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
      <table>
